# argument descriptions - input to cgen
# format:
# name  type    required	short   long    exit_function   description
#
# type (flag|var)
# required (0|1)
# exit_function (usage|version)
# short & long are the 1-char and string argument names
# description goes straight into the usage statement
#

help	flag	0	h	help	usage	print this message and exit.
version	flag	0	v	version	version	print version information and exit.
verbose	flag	0	V	verbose		print verbose status messages to console
file	var	0	f	file		specifies file to read (default = stdin)
row	var	0	r	row		specifies line number to use as header (default = 1)
label	var	1	l	label		specifies the header label to look for
delim	var	1	d	delim		specifies the file delimiter
string	var	0	s	string		allows the header line to be specified on the command-line
